Help Type: command
Command: {{ commandName }} <uri>

URI Command

Target:
  {{ uri }}

{% if target.name == "archive-scope" %}
URI type:
  Archive scope

Default behavior:
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}` enumerates archive-level objects.
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval across archive scopes.

Use when:
  - You need the archive entry point before narrowing to chapters, chunks, entities, triples, source, or summaries.

Common child targets:
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}/chapter --help`: chapter tree, chapter paths, and chapter-scoped retrieval.
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}/index --help`: archive search index status and lifecycle.
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}/meta --help`: archive metadata.
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}/cover --help`: raw cover resource.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-collection-scope" %}
URI type:
  Chapter collection scope

Default behavior:
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}` enumerates chapters.
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval to chapter objects.
  - Chapter collection scope covers the full chapter tree by default; use `--depth 0` for root-level chapters only.
  - Chapter path URIs are the public CLI handles; internal chapter ids are not command targets.

Use when:
  - You need chapter URIs, chapter readiness, or a starting point for chapter-scoped retrieval.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-scope" %}
URI type:
  Chapter scope

Default behavior:
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}` enumerates objects inside this chapter subtree.
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval inside this chapter subtree.
  - Use `--depth 0` to restrict the scope to this chapter only; `--depth 1` includes direct children.
  - The path in this URI is the public CLI handle for the chapter; internal chapter ids are not command targets.

Use when:
  - You already selected a chapter and want local source, summary, chunk, entity, or triple objects.
{% elif target.name == "chunk-scope" %}
URI type:
  Chunk scope

Default behavior:
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}` enumerates Reading Graph chunks.
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval to chunks in this scope.
{% if uriContext.isChapterQualified %}
  - This chapter-qualified scope covers the selected chapter subtree by default.
  - Use `--depth 0` for only the selected chapter, or `--depth 1` for the selected chapter plus direct children.
{% endif %}

Use when:
  - You need candidate Reading Graph chunks before selecting a concrete chunk URI.
{% if libraryContext.isLibraryWide %}
  - Open returned chunk object URIs for `evidence`, `related`, or `pack`.
{% endif %}
