{% elif target.name == "metadata-object" %}
URI type:
  Metadata object

Default behavior:
  - `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }}` reads metadata attached to this archive or object.
  - Use `--json` for a stable machine-readable metadata map.

Use when:
  - You need to read, replace, edit, clear, or delete metadata without changing the underlying source or generated graph data.

Input notes:
  - `put <key> <value>` stores a string value.
  - `put <key> --json-input <json>` stores a JSON value.
  - `--json` controls output shape; it is not JSON input.
{% endif %}

